# Crosstown Dependency Audit Acknowledgments
# Last reviewed: 2026-03-16
#
# Remaining vulnerabilities are all in transitive dependencies of:
#   - @ardrive/turbo-sdk (elliptic, bn.js, qs, undici, minimatch)
#   - @crosstown/connector (elliptic via @google-cloud/kms and ai SDK)
#   - Dev tooling (rollup, esbuild, flatted, jsondiffpatch)
#
# These cannot be resolved via pnpm.overrides because:
#   - elliptic@6.6.1: No patch available (<=6.6.1 affected, no >=6.6.2 yet)
#   - bn.js: Deeply nested in @cosmjs and arbundles chains
#   - minimatch: Locked by transitive glob versions
#   - undici: Locked by @hono/node-server peer chain
#
# Mitigations:
#   - Crosstown does NOT use elliptic directly (uses @noble/curves instead)
#   - BTP/ILP connections are internal (Docker network), not user-facing
#   - @ardrive/turbo-sdk is optional (ArDrive peer registry)
#   - Production will pin exact versions via lock file
#
# Resolved via pnpm.overrides (package.json):
#   - protobufjs >=7.2.5 (was 7.2.4, GHSA-h755-8qp9-cq85)
#   - ws >=7.5.10 (was 7.4.6, GHSA-3h5v-q93c-6h6q)
#   - body-parser >=1.20.3 (GHSA-qwcr-r2fm-qrc7)
#   - send >=0.19.0 (GHSA-m6fv-jmcg-4jfg)
#   - serve-static >=1.16.0 (GHSA-cm22-4g7w-348p)
#   - cookie >=0.7.0 (GHSA-pxg6-pf52-xh8x)
#   - path-to-regexp >=0.1.10 (ReDoS fix)
#   - express >=4.21.0 (multiple fixes)
